{
  "stem": "21731.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Then my parents moved into the same house as my grandparents lived, on the same floor, which was very convenient-- and helped my mother after she start working to earn her living, very much, because my grandparents helped.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We-- we, that means my mother, my brother, and I-- had no servants.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "My mother did everything on her own, as she was not brought up to work anywhere, but had a very good education and was also very, very gifted.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "She knew, I think, about seven languages.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So she started taking on translation, first at home.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Then she worked at various embassies.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But in the end, she got a job in a firm which was called [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "The owner was a Polish Jew, Dr.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Kreisberg, who lived in Vienna.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "He had a beautiful villa in Vienna.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "They was very rich; and was an extremely nice person, and cared from every one of his employees very much.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "So when I was, I think, about five, my mother took my brother, who was a year and a 1/2 older than I, to Strasbourg, to visit her brother, Professor Jacob Parnus, who was a professor in Strasbourg.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "There were two children our age, Gustav and Clara.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "They had a governess which was very strict with us, but we enjoyed to stay there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "On the way back, we stopped at Munich, where my mother showed us the urn with the ashes of my father.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "He was cremated in Ulm.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I don't know whether I mentioned that he died in 1912.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "So-- sorry, I forgot about that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Anyway, when we came back to Vienna, my mother started really working in this office.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And we went first to a kindergarten and then to the ordinary primary school.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
